  ('0f6n1HMHI6g', 313, 334, ARRAY['here to figure out how fast 140 is, it''s about this fast, let''s talk about this technique where you drop your bow, it''s a pretty cool little technique, and what I''m doing is I''m hovering over my strings using my bow, I have my hand totally relaxed here, so...']::text[]),
  ('0f6n1HMHI6g', 343, 360, ARRAY['it, but I''m basically, here, let me do it really slowly, a couple things that are very important here, one is you want to keep your bow hair flat, because the bow hair naturally wants to bounce, and if you''ve ever gotten nervous and you''re playing a really...']::text[]),
  ('0f6n1HMHI6g', 360, 381, ARRAY['to do is I want you to do the reverse of that. I want you to do relaxed hand and relaxed arm. But, start above the string and let it fall. And when I say let it fall, don''t let it fall like this. That''s wimpy. You get...', 'See, without anything else, if you''re just letting your bow fall, there''s no sound. What I want you to do is use your arm weight. So your arm falls with it. And also, make sure that that very first note before you have']::text[]),
  ('0f6n1HMHI6g', 381, 406, ARRAY['letting your bow fall, there''s no sound. What I want you to do is use your arm weight. So your arm falls with it. And also, make sure that that very first note before you have the ricochet... This is the ricochet.', 'Before you get to that ricochet, the note before that should be very, very, very, very short. Okay, you see that? And so, when you''re going between strings, you want to change the elevation of your arm.']::text[]),
  ('0f6n1HMHI6g', 406, 435, ARRAY['that should be very, very, very, very short. Okay, you see that? And so, when you''re going between strings, you want to change the elevation of your arm. So, if you''re on the G string, your arm should be pretty high.', 'If you''re going to do it on the D string, for instance, it''s the same concept, only I''m changing the height of my arm. Or, on the E string, or E string.']::text[]),
  ('0f6n1HMHI6g', 435, 460, ARRAY['E string. And so, that way, I don''t have to change the technique, only I have to change the angle of my arm. It does take a little bit more balance on the E string because you''re not quite vertical.', 'On the G string, it should be pretty easy, because you''re pretty much vertical. And you should be able to do this for hours. I''m not suggesting that you do that, but it should be so easy.']::text[]),
  ('1FN_xHL-u-Q', 195, 250, ARRAY['your bow, feel everything that''s happening. Feel it in your fingers, feel it in your wrist, your arm and your elbow and your forearm over here.', 'What I''m mostly concerned about is making sure that every note has a full tone to it. Maybe the reason why I don''t do scales a lot is because it''s boring. Because all you''re doing is just playing notes.']::text[]),
  ('1FN_xHL-u-Q', 250, 284, ARRAY['of something that comes to mind. What if you''re just doing something like that where you''re running up an arpeggio and you need that dexterity.', 'Well if you''ve been practicing it correctly, let''s translate that scale I was just playing into this arpeggio.']::text[]),
  ('1FN_xHL-u-Q', 497, 505, ARRAY['If it''s just a friend or something, but typically speaking, proper etiquette in a performer is to play a piece for the audience.', 'And so take that for what it''s worth and take this three octave scale for what it''s worth and see what you can do with it.']::text[]),
  ('1QFHZfQzZ0E', 196, 231, ARRAY['sounding... Instead of that, you get... And that gives the hair a chance to grip the bow and make it ring, like that. And then on that, that first chord is a little harsh. This part gives you a chance.', 'You can really be expressive here. It''s a melody, and it kind of comes out of almost nowhere.']::text[]),
  ('1QFHZfQzZ0E', 528, 539, ARRAY['And that''s the only way that I found play from this note to without getting that squeak where my pinky''s hitting the other string. So-- [MUSIC PLAYING] Whatever those notes are.']::text[]),
  ('3bAWqnjPfV4', 234, 287, ARRAY['when you''re supposed to come in. So you hear ... Now here you want to stop your bow in between each of the eighth notes. And that way you''ll mask the sound, or rather you''ll skip over the sound of the string crossing.', 'Otherwise you hear ... you''ll hear remnants of that middle string, you don''t want to do that.']::text[]),
  ('517uzXPQ3xg', 249, 274, ARRAY['because she''s just kind of thinking, "Well, do I really have a place to go? I don''t know." Now I like doing the little slur here at measure nine.', 'The way you accomplish that, so you have your B flat, then before you stop moving your bow, before you do the bow change, just start sliding your finger down nice and easy.']::text[]),
